---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How We Work - Skief Labs" description="Structured work. No chaos. No dependency. Learn how Skief Labs approaches every engagement with clarity and restraint.">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-linen pt-12 pb-16 md:pt-16 md:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center">
        <!-- Left: Text -->
        <div>
          <h1 class="page-hero-title heading-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[3.8rem] text-navy-900 mb-8 leading-[1.1] uppercase">
            Structured work. No chaos. No dependency.
          </h1>
          <div class="page-hero-body space-y-4 text-navy-900/80 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            <p>Most automation and systems projects fail not because the technology is wrong — but because the process around it is absent.</p>
            <p>Tools get added before problems are understood. Systems get built without documentation. Clients are left dependent on the people who built them.</p>
            <p>Our way of working exists to prevent exactly that.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Right: Image -->
        <div class="page-hero-image relative">
          <img src="/images/sk5.png" alt="Structured work process" class="w-full rounded-lg object-cover shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_#CFFF15]" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE PRINCIPLES — Tree/Flowchart with scroll animation -->
  <section id="principles-section" class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Top label -->
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-0" data-tree="title">
        <div class="inline-block border-2 border-navy-900 px-8 py-3 rounded shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001233]">
          <p class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-navy-900 tracking-[0.2em] text-center">Our Principles</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ===== DESKTOP TREE (hidden on mobile) ===== -->
      <div class="relative hidden md:block">
        <!-- Principle 1: RIGHT -->
        <div class="relative grid grid-cols-2 gap-0 py-8">
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 -translate-x-1/2 tree-vline" data-tree="vline1" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: top; transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);"></div>
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 w-1/2 h-0.5 -translate-y-1/2 tree-hline" data-tree="hline1" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: left; transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(0);"></div>
          <div></div>
          <div class="relative z-10 bg-linen rounded-lg p-6 border text-center max-w-xs ml-auto tree-card" data-tree="card1" style="border-color: #001233; opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
            <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Diagnosis before prescription</h3>
            <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">We don't recommend solutions before we understand the problem. This sounds obvious. In practice, most vendors skip it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Principle 2: LEFT -->
        <div class="relative grid grid-cols-2 gap-0 py-8">
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 -translate-x-1/2 tree-vline" data-tree="vline2" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: top; transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);"></div>
          <div class="absolute right-1/2 top-1/2 w-1/2 h-0.5 -translate-y-1/2 tree-hline" data-tree="hline2" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: right; transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(0);"></div>
          <div class="relative z-10 bg-linen rounded-lg p-6 border text-center max-w-xs tree-card" data-tree="card2" style="border-color: #001233; opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
            <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Judgment before automation</h3>
            <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Not everything should be automated. We're deliberate about what stays human — and why. Restraint is part of what you're hiring.</p>
          </div>
          <div></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Principle 3: RIGHT -->
        <div class="relative grid grid-cols-2 gap-0 py-8">
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 -translate-x-1/2 tree-vline" data-tree="vline3" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: top; transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);"></div>
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 w-1/2 h-0.5 -translate-y-1/2 tree-hline" data-tree="hline3" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: left; transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(0);"></div>
          <div></div>
          <div class="relative z-10 bg-linen rounded-lg p-6 border text-center max-w-xs ml-auto tree-card" data-tree="card3" style="border-color: #001233; opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
            <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Clarity over complexity</h3>
            <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">If a system can't be explained simply, it isn't finished. Every workflow we build can be understood by the people who use it.</p>
