          <div class="relative z-10 bg-linen rounded-lg p-6 border text-center max-w-xs tree-card" data-tree="card4" style="border-color: #001233; opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
            <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Ownership by design</h3>
            <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Nothing we build should require us to stay involved. Full documentation, clean handoff, zero dependency — by default, not on request.</p>
          </div>
          <div></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Principle 5: RIGHT -->
        <div class="relative grid grid-cols-2 gap-0 py-8">
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 -translate-x-1/2 tree-vline" data-tree="vline5" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: top; transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);"></div>
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 w-1/2 h-0.5 -translate-y-1/2 tree-hline" data-tree="hline5" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: left; transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(0);"></div>
          <div></div>
          <div class="relative z-10 bg-linen rounded-lg p-6 border text-center max-w-xs ml-auto tree-card" data-tree="card5" style="border-color: #001233; opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
            <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Fixed scope. Fixed expectations.</h3>
            <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">No drifting projects. No surprise invoices. No open-ended engagements that expand without your consent.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Final vertical line to bottom box -->
        <div class="relative" style="height: 60px;">
          <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 -translate-x-1/2 tree-vline" data-tree="vline6" style="background-color: #001233; transform-origin: top; transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ===== MOBILE: Simple stacked cards (hidden on desktop) ===== -->
      <div class="md:hidden space-y-4 mt-8">
        <div class="bg-linen rounded-lg p-5 border text-center" style="border-color: #001233;">
          <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Diagnosis before prescription</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">We don't recommend solutions before we understand the problem. This sounds obvious. In practice, most vendors skip it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-linen rounded-lg p-5 border text-center" style="border-color: #001233;">
          <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Judgment before automation</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Not everything should be automated. We're deliberate about what stays human — and why. Restraint is part of what you're hiring.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-linen rounded-lg p-5 border text-center" style="border-color: #001233;">
          <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Clarity over complexity</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">If a system can't be explained simply, it isn't finished. Every workflow we build can be understood by the people who use it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-linen rounded-lg p-5 border text-center" style="border-color: #001233;">
          <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Ownership by design</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Nothing we build should require us to stay involved. Full documentation, clean handoff, zero dependency — by default, not on request.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-linen rounded-lg p-5 border text-center" style="border-color: #001233;">
          <h3 class="text-navy-900 text-base font-semibold mb-1">Fixed scope. Fixed expectations.</h3>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">No drifting projects. No surprise invoices. No open-ended engagements that expand without your consent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bottom summary — desktop: animated, mobile: always visible -->
      <div class="hidden md:flex justify-center mt-0 tree-card" data-tree="summary" style="opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);">
        <div class="inline-block border-2 border-navy-900 px-8 py-3 rounded bg-linen shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001233]">
          <p class="text-navy-900/80 text-base text-center italic">These apply to every engagement, regardless of size or service.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="md:hidden flex justify-center mt-6">
        <div class="inline-block border-2 border-navy-900 px-6 py-3 rounded bg-linen shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001233]">
          <p class="text-navy-900/80 text-sm text-center italic">These apply to every engagement, regardless of size or service.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE ENGAGEMENT -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-[2.2rem] text-navy-900 mb-4 leading-[1.25] tracking-[-0.02em]">
          The Engagement
        </h2>
        <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-base md:text-lg max-w-xl">
          Once there's a clear fit, the path differs by service — but the principles are the same.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="service-card rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10 border-2 bg-linen">
          <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-navy-900 tracking-[0.2em] mb-6">For Data Intelligence</h3>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-navy-900/80 text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>We scope the build based on what the discovery conversation reveals. Work is fixed in scope, time-bound, and fully documented.</p>
            <p>At completion, you own the system entirely — transferred access, clean documentation, logic any competent partner or internal hire could maintain.</p>
            <p>Some clients have us continue operating the system on an ongoing basis. Others take it and run it themselves. Either way is fine. The goal was never dependency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10 border-2 bg-linen">
          <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-sm text-navy-900 tracking-[0.2em] mb-6">For Sales Acceleration</h3>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-navy-900/80 text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>We start with a pilot — a defined scope and fixed price that builds the system and runs it through the first weeks of live execution.</p>
            <p>Most clients move to an ongoing monthly retainer from there, where we continue running and optimizing the outbound motion.</p>
            <p>There's no obligation to continue beyond the pilot, and no lock-in at any point. The system — and everything in it — remains yours.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer Note -->
      <div class="pt-8 mt-10 border-t border-navy-900/10 flex items-center gap-5">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-900/5 shrink-0">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#001233" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/>
            <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="text-lg text-navy-900/50 whitespace-nowrap">
          In both cases: nothing is built before the scope is clear. No surprises mid-engagement. No invoices for work you didn't agree to.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WORKING WITH US FEELS LIKE -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Heading block -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="inline-block">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-0.5 bg-navy-900"></div>
              <p class="subhead-condensed text-xs text-navy-900 tracking-[0.2em]">The Experience</p>
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-[2.2rem] text-navy-900 mb-3 leading-[1.25] tracking-[-0.02em] text-center">
              What working with us feels like
            </h2>
            <div class="flex justify-end">
              <div class="w-12 h-0.5 bg-navy-900"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-10"></div>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-navy-900/70 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-center">
          <p class="text-navy-900 font-serif text-xl italic">Clients describe it as calm.</p>
          <p>There are no status meetings held for the sake of appearances. No performative reporting designed to justify the invoice. No pressure to expand scope beyond what makes sense.</p>
          <p>You'll always know what we're doing and why. Decisions are explained, not handed down. Progress is visible, not summarized at the end of the month.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Callout box -->
        <div class="flex items-stretch justify-center gap-4 mt-10">
          <div class="w-0.5 bg-navy-900 rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <p class="text-navy-900/70 text-sm italic leading-relaxed py-1 text-center">We build what needs to exist — and stop.</p>
          <div class="w-0.5 bg-navy-900 rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="cta-box rounded-2xl overflow-hidden grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[38%_62%] bg-navy-900">
        <div class="cta-image-col">
          <img src="/images/sk3.jpg" alt="Discovery call" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-center px-8 py-12 md:px-12 md:py-16 text-center">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-[1.75rem] lg:text-[2rem] text-linen mb-4 leading-[1.25] tracking-[-0.02em]">
            <span class="neon-underline">One entry point. Always the same.</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-linen/80 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8 italic">
            A 30-minute discovery call.
          </p>
          <p class="text-linen/60 text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Not a pitch. Not a free audit. Not a commitment.
          </p>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
            A focused conversation to understand where friction is concentrated in your business — and whether we're the right people to remove it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-linen/70 text-base leading-relaxed mb-10">
            Either way, you leave the call with more clarity than you arrived with.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a href="/contact" class="cta-book-btn btn-primary inline-flex items-center gap-2">
              Book a 30-minute discovery call
              <span class="cta-arrow text-lg inline-block transition-transform duration-300">→</span>
            </a>
            <p class="text-linen/50 text-sm italic">No pitch. No obligation. Just clarity.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .tree-vline, .tree-hline, .tree-card {
    transition: transform 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1), opacity 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }
  [data-tree="title"] {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(10px);
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
  }
  [data-tree="title"].tree-visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
  .tree-vline.tree-visible {
    transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(1) !important;
  }
  .tree-hline.tree-visible {
    transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(1) !important;
  }
  .tree-card.tree-visible {
    opacity: 1 !important;
    transform: translateY(0) !important;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Scroll-driven tree animation for the Principles section (one-way — stays visible once revealed)
  const section = document.getElementById('principles-section');
  if (section) {
    const steps = [
      'title',
      'vline1', 'hline1', 'card1',
      'vline2', 'hline2', 'card2',
      'vline3', 'hline3', 'card3',
      'vline4', 'hline4', 'card4',
      'vline5', 'hline5', 'card5',
      'vline6', 'summary'
    ];

    const elements = steps.map(s => section.querySelector(`[data-tree="${s}"]`)).filter(Boolean) as HTMLElement[];
    let maxRevealed = -1; // Track highest revealed index (never goes back)

    function updateTree() {
      const rect = section!.getBoundingClientRect();
      const viewH = window.innerHeight;
      const scrolled = viewH - rect.top;
      const totalRange = rect.height + viewH * 0.3;
      const progress = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, scrolled / totalRange));
      const stepSize = 1 / elements.length;

      elements.forEach((el, i) => {
        const threshold = i * stepSize;
        if (progress > threshold && i > maxRevealed) {
          maxRevealed = i;
          el.classList.add('tree-visible');
        }
      });
    }

    window.addEventListener('scroll', updateTree, { passive: true });
    updateTree();
  }
</script>
